<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>This is the chilling moment a woman recorded a stranger harassing her on the street before he groped her breasts, according to police.</p>

<p>The 30-year-old filmed the clip as she walked through Steinway Street in Astoria, Queens, at around 7.05pm on Saturday.</p>

<p>The suspect smirked and waved at the woman, who was walking alone, before he allegedly began shouting: 'Where are you going?'</p>

<p>The police have now released the woman's own cell phone footage after asking for the public's help in identifying the man.</p>

<p>The 30-year-old woman filmed the stranger (pictured) after walking through Steinway Street in Astoria, Queens, at around 7.05pm on Saturday </p>

<p>In the video, a man can be seen wearing a beige button-down shirt, black jeans and sneakers as he walks down the pavement with a brown leather satchel across his body. </p>

<p>He crosses the road before stopping outside a clothes shop to turn around and face the woman.</p>

<p>The man smirks and waves toward the camera before even doffing an imaginary cap in her direction. </p>

<p>He then strolls back across the street toward the woman once again which is where the video ends.</p>

<p>In the video the man (pictured) can be seen smirking and waving toward the camera before doffing an imaginary cap in her direction</p>

<p>This is when the suspect is alleged to have grabbed both of the woman's breasts before walking off when the victim screamed, police said.</p>

<p>Authorities are now appealing for the public's help in identifying the alleged attacker.  </p>

<p>The suspect is described as being in his early 30s with a high hairstyle and a small ponytail.   </p>

<p>Anyone with information is asked to call Crime Stoppers at (800) 577-TIPS.</p>
